-- Thailand’s IRPC Said to Seek Low-Sulfur Oil Supply for November
-- B y   R a m s e y   A l - R i k a b i
-- 2012-09-18T04:05:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-18/thailand-s-irpc-said-to-seek-low-sulfur-oil-supply-for-november.html
IRPC Pcl (IRPC) , an oil refiner and
petrochemical maker based in Thailand, is seeking to buy between
600,000 and 1 million barrels of low-sulfur, or sweet, crude for
delivery during early November to its 215,000 barrel-a-day plant
in Rayong province, according to three people who participate in
the market, asking not to be identified because they aren’t
authorized to speak to the media.  The tender closes today at noon, Bangkok time, with
validity until 6 p.m. tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ramsey Al-Rikabi in Singapore at 
 ralrikabi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
